sections.content: The property covered under Gift Settlement Deed No. 534 of 2026, dated 24/Jan/2026, executed by Palthiya Chandu Lal, in favour of his Wife, Mudu Aswini, towards the property admeasuring an extent of 338.8 Sq. Yds. (or) 3049.20 Sq. Ft., bearing house number 1-159, Assessment number 556, comprised in survey number 77-4, situated in Kummarikuntla Village and Grama Panchayath, A. Konduru Mandal, within the District of NTR, registered at sub-registrar office Nunna (628), is bounded as follows: North by: Panchayathi Road South by: Road East by: Site of Donor West by: Site of Lavuri Anji.

(A) As per Registered Documents: 1. The property in survey number 77-4, bearing house no. 1-159, Assessment number 556, situated in Kummarikuntla Village, measuring about 338.8 Sq. Yds. (or) 3049.20 Sq. Ft., was originally owned by Palthiya Chandu Lal, who acquired the property through inheritance from his ancestors. [Ref. Deed] 2. The aforementioned Palthiya Chandu Lal, executed a Gift Settlement Deed on 24/Jan/2026, registered as document No. 534 of 2026, before the SRO Nunna, in favour of his Wife, Mudu Aswini, towards the property measuring 338.8 Sq. Yds. (or) 3049.20 Sq. Ft., bearing house no. 1-159, Assessment number 556, comprised in survey no. 77-4, situated at Kummarikuntla Village. Note: The pledging document was registered on 24/Jan/2026, which is less than three months. Hence, F.I. is to obtain internal approval from appropriate authority before disbursement of the loan. (B) Additional Documents Supporting the Title : The Property Tax Receipt No. 232328, dated 29/Oct/2025, imprinted by the Kummarakuntla Grama Panchayath Secretary, discloses that Palthiya Chandu Lal, has paid property tax for the period 2024 to 2025 towards house number 1-159 and Assessment number 556. Note: It is advisable to verify that the tax is paid up-to-date towards the schedule property.

The property tax receipt attached discloses that Palthiya Chandu Lal, is the taxpayer, hence, it is presumed that the mutation proceedings were not concluded in the name of the current owner Mudu Aswini.
